pull_request.title: Fix demo_party field mapping for natural language queries
pull_request.body:
# Fix demo_party field mapping for natural language queries ## Summary This PR fixes an issue where natural language queries about political party affiliation were generating incorrect SQL. Specifically, when users asked questions like "how many democrats live on Dryden Road in Bernardsville?", the system would convert "democrats" to "Democratic" instead of the correct database value "DEMOCRAT". The fix involves three key changes: 1. **Enhanced system prompt** with explicit schema constraints for the `demo_party` field 2. **Intelligent field mappings** to handle common party name variations 3. **Improved SQL transformation logic** to properly handle quoted string value replacements ## Review & Testing Checklist for Human **âš ï¸ Critical Testing Required (3 items)** - [ ] **Test the original problematic query**: Submit "how many democrats live on Dryden Road in Bernardsville?" in the Streamlit app and verify the generated SQL uses `demo_party = 'DEMOCRAT'` instead of `demo_party = 'Democratic'` - [ ] **Verify existing functionality**: Test other party-related queries (e.g., "how many Republicans are in Somerset County?") to ensure they still work correctly and generate proper SQL - [ ] **Test edge cases**: Try variations like "Democratic voters", "republican party", "Independent voters" to ensure the field mappings handle different capitalizations and word forms correctly **Recommended Test Plan:** 1. Start the Streamlit app: `streamlit run agents/nj_voter_chat_adk/app_streamlit.py` 2. Test the original query and check the debug output in terminal for the generated SQL 3. Try several variations of party names with different capitalizations 4. Test non-party queries to ensure no regressions were introduced --- ### Diagram ```mermaid %%{ init : { "theme" : "default" }}%% graph TD User["User Query:
'how many democrats live
on Dryden Road?'"] --> StreamlitApp["agents/nj_voter_chat_adk/
app_streamlit.py"]:::context StreamlitApp --> Agent["agents/nj_voter_chat_adk/
agent.py"]:::context Agent --> SystemPrompt["config.py
SYSTEM_PROMPT"]:::major-edit Agent --> BigQueryTool["bigquery_tool.py
BigQueryReadOnlyTool"]:::major-edit BigQueryTool --> FieldMappings["FIELD_MAPPINGS
Dictionary"]:::major-edit BigQueryTool --> ApplyMappings["_apply_field_mappings()
Method"]:::major-edit FieldMappings --> SQL["Generated SQL:
demo_party = 'DEMOCRAT'"]:::context ApplyMappings --> SQL subgraph Legend L1["Major Edit"]:::major-edit L2["Minor Edit"]:::minor-edit L3["Context/No Edit"]:::context end classDef major-edit fill:#90EE90 classDef minor-edit fill:#87CEEB classDef context fill:#F5F5F5 ``` ### Notes - **Testing limitation**: I was able to verify the field mapping logic works correctly through unit tests, but the end-to-end Streamlit test was slow to respond during development. The core transformation logic is solid but needs human verification of the full user experience. - **Backward compatibility**: The changes are additive and shouldn't break existing queries, but thorough testing is recommended. - **Case handling**: The new logic handles case-insensitive input but produces the correct case-sensitive database values. **Link to Devin run**: https://app.devin.ai/sessions/8b378d6d45da45709292d9c070916ce3 **Requested by**: Greg (gregtusar@gmail.com)

pull_request.title: some minor improvements
pull_request.body:
This pull request introduces several improvements and new features to the codebase, focusing on enhancing the voting experience on questions and replies, improving developer experience with new seeders and factories, updating environment configuration, and adding new styling. The most significant changes include the addition of AJAX support for voting, the creation of database seeders and factories for easier testing and development, and updates to environment and documentation files.

**Voting System Enhancements**
* Added AJAX support to upvote/downvote methods in both `QuestionController` and `ReplyController`, allowing for real-time updates and the ability to remove votes (toggle upvote/downvote), with clear user feedback messages. Also, now tracks the user's vote status for questions and replies. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-6c4cca9be8aad3767012d6cae332e96c81e086135267068b8093914683306f41L74-R92) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-6c4cca9be8aad3767012d6cae332e96c81e086135267068b8093914683306f41L86-R138) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-6c4cca9be8aad3767012d6cae332e96c81e086135267068b8093914683306f41L113-R184) [[4]](diffhunk://#diff-44c580f97a556bbc32180844fd34a6d51d0708cec590a8d3f34a060d0c04f38fL48-R82) [[5]](diffhunk://#diff-44c580f97a556bbc32180844fd34a6d51d0708cec590a8d3f34a060d0c04f38fL73-R128)
* Reduced the number of most used tags displayed on the question index page from 10 to 5 for better UI clarity.

**Database and Seeding Improvements**
* Added new model factories for `Question`, `Reply`, and `Vote` to simplify the creation of test data. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-f23a86e736f1e9ed0eb300ed668d158f247eac81f8aa5ffa1a416c3a50bc38caR1-R26) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-d847605951895b0c2e1ae8b1c1446fe0e4a7fac20ca8660d7332af8f8d21c357R1-R23) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-b06c3cb859e1441f0d548c7cc1d7e27019a56896b86d488d54ad327011c26ee6R1-R23)
* Introduced a comprehensive `DummyDataSeeder` for populating the database with sample users, questions, and replies, and updated `DatabaseSeeder` to use it. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-c3757c27404c304baef34c2e2bacd21e7eb3beba8af5e1373d193c187c993e89R1-R89) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-ccad8b4ee6013765c2bc672aa0515f8e99e42949c914cce01e0cb2b4e882775dL16-R16)

**Styling and UI**
* Added a new `resources/css/index.css` file with Tailwind-based and custom styles for improved UI consistency and dark mode support.
* Minor cleanup in `login.css` by removing an unused Google Fonts import.

**Configuration and Documentation Updates**
* Updated `.env.example` to use MySQL instead of SQLite and switched mail settings to use Gmail SMTP for a more realistic development environment. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-a3046da0d15a27e89f2afe639b25748a7ad4d9290af3e7b1b6c1a5533c8f0a8cL22-R27) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-a3046da0d15a27e89f2afe639b25748a7ad4d9290af3e7b1b6c1a5533c8f0a8cL49-R55)
* Improved project setup instructions in `README.md`, including running the queue worker and formatting steps as a numbered list.
* Added the `mallardduck/blade-lucide-icons` package to `composer.json` for icon support.

## Summary by Sourcery

Apply ground friction to standing entities in the DBSP motion circuit and update tests and documentation to reflect this behaviour.

New Features:
- Scale horizontal velocities by (1 âˆ’ GROUND_FRICTION) for standing entities in the motion circuit

Enhancements:
- Document the ground friction operator in the physics design docs and mark the roadmap entry as complete
- Ensure all motion logic, including friction, is computed within the DBSP circuit without external duplication

Tests:
- Update existing DBSP and BDD tests to expect reduced velocities due to ground friction
- Add parameterized tests for standing friction with positive, negative, and zero velocities
